summary:
Please follow me on Instagram @chrisdebode
Award winning documentary photographer/filmmaker specialized in contemporary issues. Many years of experience in travelling all over the planet finding compelling stories which need to be told. Published his work in many leading magazines/newspapers like National Geographic, der Spiegel, Liberation, Geo, Internazionale, Granta, the Sunday Times magazine etc etc. Latest movie "Living on Scrap" commissioned by Save the Children. Also for Save currently working on "Dream pictures" Visualizing dreams of children all over the world. 
Chris is commishioned by several NGO's like Save the Children, MSF, Greenpeace, Cordaid, St Vluchteling, VSO and Panos.
Several UN branches like UNFPA and UNHCR and WHO work with him.
Apart from making pictures Chris was the program director of the international Slovenian Photofestival Fotopub. 
He has broad experience in mentoring workshops in several countries educating photographers on all levels focusing on story telling in pictures. Among his clients are World Press Photo.
Chris is invited on many festivals to give lectures on his work and his broad experience.
